WEBVTT

00:08.708 --> 00:10.708
[pulsing music playing]

00:38.916 --> 00:40.916
♪ ♪

00:48.000 --> 00:50.000
<i>[footsteps thudding]</i>

00:51.666 --> 00:53.374
<i>[creature growling]</i>

00:53.375 --> 00:55.957
- [snarling]
- [sobbing]

00:55.958 --> 00:58.250
[father] Just keep your eyes closed.

01:02.500 --> 01:05.000
[mother] It's going to be all right.

01:05.125 --> 01:07.875
[Yi Xing] <i>I was orphaned by a living city.</i>

01:09.000 --> 01:12.499
<i>Ever changing, always in motion.</i>

01:12.500 --> 01:16.457
<i>A city controlled by a great machine.</i>

01:16.458 --> 01:18.250
<i>The Tiangong.</i>

01:28.250 --> 01:30.457
<i>The city is supposed to care for</i>

01:30.458 --> 01:31.958
<i>and protect us...</i>

01:36.250 --> 01:38.707
<i>...but something is wrong.</i>

01:38.708 --> 01:41.375
<i>The mechanical mind
that rules the city is failing.</i>

01:42.750 --> 01:45.665
<i>A mad god,
for whom everything is just a game,</i>

01:45.666 --> 01:48.666
<i>fortified within the Palace of the Tiangong.</i>

01:50.375 --> 01:53.790
<i>How do you take revenge on a god?</i>

01:53.791 --> 01:56.040
[mad beggar shudders] <i>No.</i>

01:56.041 --> 01:58.957
No, no, no, no, no, boy.
Not in there. Never.

01:58.958 --> 02:00.332
You...

02:00.333 --> 02:03.915
You, you're not going in there, are you?

02:03.916 --> 02:05.208
I am.

02:06.958 --> 02:10.165
Then... then you're crazy!

02:10.166 --> 02:13.749
You'll end up just
like the rest of us. [shuddering]

02:13.750 --> 02:17.332
We'll save a place for you!

02:17.333 --> 02:18.666
[beggar laughing]

02:21.083 --> 02:23.416
[tense music playing]

02:29.041 --> 02:31.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:37.708 --> 02:40.707
You're here to challenge the Tiangong.

02:40.708 --> 02:42.208
Yes.

02:43.291 --> 02:44.499
You're young.

02:44.500 --> 02:47.582
I'm the best Weiqi player in Chang'an.

02:47.583 --> 02:50.082
And arrogant as well.

02:50.083 --> 02:51.875
Wonderful.

02:52.958 --> 02:54.541
Come in, come in.

02:56.041 --> 02:57.916
We have a game to play.

02:58.916 --> 03:00.916
[somber music playing]

03:08.541 --> 03:10.291
[rumbling]

03:11.291 --> 03:17.249
From this place, The Tiangong observes
and controls every aspect of the city;

03:17.250 --> 03:21.790
everything that has been,
everything that will be.

03:21.791 --> 03:25.832
"You may face the Tiangong
in any game of your choosing."

03:25.833 --> 03:27.415
[Yi Xing] I know the rules.

03:27.416 --> 03:29.665
[Tiangong] Then you know
I have to tell them to you.

03:29.666 --> 03:32.040
[rhythmic thudding]

03:32.041 --> 03:34.624
"You'll have only one chance.

03:34.625 --> 03:37.832
As the all-knowing Tiangong
is responsible

03:37.833 --> 03:40.415
for the movements of our great city,

03:40.416 --> 03:44.041
and his moments
in the river of time are precious."

03:48.208 --> 03:51.457
"If you defeat the Tiangong,
you will take its power,

03:51.458 --> 03:54.665
its glory, and its burden.

03:54.666 --> 03:56.957
The fate of this city."

03:56.958 --> 03:58.915
But you won't win.

03:58.916 --> 04:02.665
Every last person
who's faced the Tiangong has come away

04:02.666 --> 04:04.875
stark raving mad.

04:05.958 --> 04:07.999
<i>- [mad man clamoring]</i>
- I know that.

04:08.000 --> 04:10.999
But I also know you're losing control.

04:11.000 --> 04:13.332
This city is crumbling.

04:13.333 --> 04:15.832
As the Tiangong’s always known it would.

04:15.833 --> 04:20.707
When I say that I know everything,
I mean every thing.

04:20.708 --> 04:23.957
All of history, every cause

04:23.958 --> 04:25.249
and every effect:

04:25.250 --> 04:27.999
One domino knocks down the next.

04:28.000 --> 04:31.457
Even a human could understand this.

04:31.458 --> 04:34.958
But here is the world the Tiangong sees.

04:36.041 --> 04:39.583
Every fact, every moment.

04:40.583 --> 04:43.874
One thing leads to the next,
and to the next,

04:43.875 --> 04:47.458
and to what comes undeniably after that.

04:49.041 --> 04:51.165
For the Tiangong, there's no difference

04:51.166 --> 04:55.000
between remembering the past
and imagining the future.

04:57.083 --> 04:59.540
I know your every move,

04:59.541 --> 05:02.707
long before you make it.

05:02.708 --> 05:05.333
Okay, let's play.

05:15.458 --> 05:18.874
If you're so superior to humans,
why would you want to look like us?

05:18.875 --> 05:20.582
It's for you.

05:20.583 --> 05:23.957
But I'm afraid I have no face
that's not a disguise.

05:23.958 --> 05:27.624
How would you like me to appear?
You could play against yourself.

05:27.625 --> 05:32.374
Or any of the Weiqi masters
you studied with and long ago surpassed.

05:32.375 --> 05:34.458
Or yourself as a child.

05:37.666 --> 05:40.124
Your whole life is here.

05:40.125 --> 05:42.082
Everything you ever were,

05:42.083 --> 05:44.416
everything you'll ever be.

05:46.625 --> 05:51.291
I know where you begin and where you end.

05:55.125 --> 05:57.041
Pick a hand.

05:58.125 --> 06:00.332
You'll choose black.

06:00.333 --> 06:02.624
And I play white.

06:02.625 --> 06:05.791
Place the first stone.

06:08.833 --> 06:10.833
[intriguing music playing]

06:26.750 --> 06:29.040
Why do you even bother playing games?

06:29.041 --> 06:31.582
If you know how everything turns out.

06:31.583 --> 06:34.874
I only know what will happen
because it will happen.

06:34.875 --> 06:37.332
So you control everything.

06:37.333 --> 06:39.249
I control nothing.

06:39.250 --> 06:41.957
But you move the city.

06:41.958 --> 06:45.124
As the Moon moves the tides.

06:45.125 --> 06:48.833
Cause and effect, that is all.

06:53.000 --> 06:55.999
You're going to tell me why you're here.

06:56.000 --> 06:58.290
Don't use that face.

06:58.291 --> 06:59.791
As you wish.

07:02.041 --> 07:03.915
[Yi Xing] You killed my parents.

07:03.916 --> 07:07.249
You have not been paying attention.

07:07.250 --> 07:08.541
Look.

07:10.291 --> 07:11.624
I know how this ends.

07:11.625 --> 07:13.916
- [creature growling nearby]
- Stop.

07:14.916 --> 07:17.207
[creature snarling]

07:17.208 --> 07:19.833
I said, stop!

07:27.000 --> 07:29.957
There was an earthquake.
A demonic incursion.

07:29.958 --> 07:32.958
The demons had to be
returned to the underworld.

07:36.250 --> 07:37.665
Play your stone.

07:37.666 --> 07:40.207
You could have done anything.

07:40.208 --> 07:42.665
You didn't have to kill my parents.

07:42.666 --> 07:46.499
If the tide rolled in
and drowned your parents,

07:46.500 --> 07:49.291
would you seek revenge against the Moon?

07:50.375 --> 07:52.250
[Yi Xing] Yes.

07:53.375 --> 07:55.957
[Tiangong] You'd rather make
the Moon an enemy

07:55.958 --> 07:59.125
than admit that cause precedes effect.

08:04.125 --> 08:06.749
You still don't believe me.

08:06.750 --> 08:11.249
Here. This mirror reflects
one second into the future.

08:11.250 --> 08:13.832
[echoing] Nothing happens by chance.

08:13.833 --> 08:16.499
I could set the mirror
two minutes into the future.

08:16.500 --> 08:18.249
Or an hour.

08:18.250 --> 08:20.207
Do you want to see how this ends?

08:20.208 --> 08:24.707
And then drive yourself crazy
trying to avoid the inevitable?

08:24.708 --> 08:27.749
This is the point where people
start to go insane.

08:27.750 --> 08:30.457
When you face absolute proof
that you have no control.

08:30.458 --> 08:33.666
Your brain will try to convince
itself that it's making choices.

08:33.791 --> 08:35.915
That you have free will.

08:35.916 --> 08:39.165
That you're not just one more cog
necessarily spinning

08:39.166 --> 08:42.499
in a complex
but utterly predictable machine.

08:42.500 --> 08:44.124
You only think that way...

08:44.125 --> 08:47.540
[echoing] You only think that way
because you are a machine.

08:47.541 --> 08:48.999
And you're not?

08:49.000 --> 08:50.999
Some machines are made of metal,

08:51.000 --> 08:53.124
some machines are made of flesh.

08:53.125 --> 08:57.125
The city of Chang'an is made of both.

08:58.333 --> 09:00.333
[eerie music playing]

09:07.625 --> 09:09.540
Wait. What?

09:09.541 --> 09:11.249
[people screaming]

09:11.250 --> 09:12.915
Is that real?

09:12.916 --> 09:14.415
How could you not know?

09:14.416 --> 09:17.790
We are playing for control
of the movements of Chang'an.

09:17.791 --> 09:20.624
That means we are playing with Chang'an.

09:20.625 --> 09:23.707
What we do here has consequences.

09:23.708 --> 09:25.499
[Yi Xing] Stop. Stop it.

09:25.500 --> 09:27.499
[tense music playing]

09:27.500 --> 09:28.957
There are people out there.

09:28.958 --> 09:32.415
And this is the other point
at which people lose their minds.

09:32.416 --> 09:35.582
To be stuck in a destiny
you can't control,

09:35.583 --> 09:38.499
but still responsible
for the lives of thousands.

09:38.500 --> 09:41.165
[echoes] You can't be perfect.

09:41.166 --> 09:42.499
You can't know everything.

09:42.500 --> 09:43.957
And you're failing. You're falling apart.

09:43.958 --> 09:45.457
You're falling apart.

09:45.458 --> 09:49.124
This city has been falling apart
more and more my entire life.

09:49.125 --> 09:51.290
Nothing lasts forever.

09:51.291 --> 09:55.125
My end, like yours,
is built into my design.

09:56.333 --> 09:58.665
Of course, if it's too much for you,

09:58.666 --> 10:00.957
- why not just stay in the past?
- [distant laughter]

10:00.958 --> 10:04.332
I have it all here.

10:04.333 --> 10:06.082
Because they're dead.

10:06.083 --> 10:07.540
[Tiangong] No.

10:07.541 --> 10:09.832
They're only in the past.

10:09.833 --> 10:11.749
- They're gone.
- So certain,

10:11.750 --> 10:15.375
when you can't even bear to look at it.

10:16.375 --> 10:18.874
You ruined my life.

10:18.875 --> 10:22.665
You make me an enemy so you can hate me.

10:22.666 --> 10:27.707
Because once you start hating,
you can stop thinking.

10:27.708 --> 10:30.625
[somber music playing]

10:34.333 --> 10:36.000
So show me.

10:39.125 --> 10:41.249
Show me how they died.

10:41.250 --> 10:44.249
[Tiangong] <i>The earthquake
tore the city open,</i>

10:44.250 --> 10:47.083
<i>releasing demons from the underworld.</i>

10:48.875 --> 10:50.291
[dramatic music playing]

10:55.791 --> 10:57.083
[growling]

11:17.250 --> 11:19.957
[people screaming]

11:19.958 --> 11:22.666
[low roar]

11:28.250 --> 11:30.124
<i>Citizens like your parents</i>

11:30.125 --> 11:32.124
<i>tried to fight them off,</i>

11:32.125 --> 11:34.207
<i>- but there were too many.</i>
- [crying softly]

11:34.208 --> 11:36.665
[Yi Xing's father] Just keep
your eyes closed.

11:36.666 --> 11:39.124
[Yi Xing's mother] It's going to be
all right.

11:39.125 --> 11:40.707
[somber music playing]

11:40.708 --> 11:42.791
[demon roaring]

11:52.791 --> 11:55.499
[Tiangong] <i>The Tiangong gave up
a piece of the city that day</i>

11:55.500 --> 11:58.249
<i>to preserve the whole.</i>

11:58.250 --> 12:00.790
My parents saved me.

12:00.791 --> 12:03.207
They chose to sacrifice themselves.

12:03.208 --> 12:04.874
It had to happen.

12:04.875 --> 12:07.290
Because they made it happen.

12:07.291 --> 12:10.832
How can you still believe that?

12:10.833 --> 12:12.708
[dramatic music playing]

12:20.708 --> 12:23.458
Because I'm making the same choice.

12:27.541 --> 12:29.874
The board represents Chang'an,

12:29.875 --> 12:31.665
with us at its heart.

12:31.666 --> 12:34.458
[soaring music playing]

12:39.500 --> 12:40.665
What are you doing?

12:40.666 --> 12:42.874
You would say,

12:42.875 --> 12:45.500
exactly what I'm here to do.

12:47.125 --> 12:49.832
Stop. Stop this.

12:49.833 --> 12:52.415
You would sacrifice yourself?

12:52.416 --> 12:56.124
I can't win,
but I can choose how this ends.

12:56.125 --> 12:59.457
Despite everything I've shown you,

12:59.458 --> 13:03.041
you still somehow believe
you're making a choice?

13:07.625 --> 13:11.458
Play your stone.

13:16.750 --> 13:18.250
[Tiangong] Then...

13:19.666 --> 13:21.583
...I concede.

13:23.958 --> 13:25.958
[contemplative music playing]

13:29.541 --> 13:33.625
This was a... fun game.

13:36.875 --> 13:38.875
♪ ♪

13:47.958 --> 13:49.791
[choral music playing]

14:10.041 --> 14:12.374
[mad beggar] What did you do?

14:12.375 --> 14:15.165
- I won.
- No.

14:15.166 --> 14:17.375
Not possible.

14:18.708 --> 14:20.790
Impossible...

14:20.791 --> 14:22.665
Inevitable...

14:22.666 --> 14:25.957
[mad beggar] But... what happens now?

14:25.958 --> 14:27.875
Exactly.

14:32.416 --> 14:34.416
[contemplative music playing]

14:46.083 --> 14:48.083
[low rumble]

14:50.875 --> 14:52.875
[uplifting music playing]

15:17.458 --> 15:19.458
♪ ♪

15:30.875 --> 15:33.958
You're here to challenge the Tiangong.

15:35.125 --> 15:36.874
[Yi Xing] Yes.

15:36.875 --> 15:38.958
- [soft clattering]
- [contemplative music playing]

15:48.291 --> 15:50.291
♪ ♪

16:19.958 --> 16:21.916
♪ ♪

16:44.458 --> 16:46.458
♪ ♪
